   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SynID — Zero-Shot Identity-Consistent Image Generation\n",
    "\n",
    "Generate multiple consistent images of the same character from a text description alone.\n",
    "No real reference photos. No dataset. No pretraining. ~5 minutes on T4 GPU.\n",
    "\n",
    "[![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/badge/github-SynID-181717?logo=github)](https://github.com/rxbinsingh/SynID)\n",
    "[![HuggingFace](https://img.shields.io/badge/🤗%20HuggingFace-SynID-FFD21E)](https://huggingface.co/rxbinsingh/SynID)\n",
    "[![Paper](https://img.shields.io/badge/paper-ResearchGate-00CCBB)](https://doi.org/10.13140/RG.2.2.30671.85925)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Runtime:** Make sure you are using a GPU runtime. Go to `Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Install dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q gradio diffusers transformers accelerate controlnet_aux \\\n",
    "    safetensors huggingface_hub insightface onnxruntime torchvision"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 — Clone the SynID repository"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!git clone https://github.com/rxbinsingh/SynID\n",
    "%cd SynID"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 — Launch the Gradio UI\n",
    "\n",
    "This will load all pipeline definitions. Click **Load Pipelines** in the UI to download and initialize the models (DreamShaper, ControlNet, CLIP, OpenPose). This takes ~2 minutes on first run.\n",
    "\n",
    "A public share URL will appear — use it to open the app on your phone."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "exec(open('synid_ui.py').read())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Alternative — Use the backend directly (no UI)\n",
    "\n",
    "If you prefer scripting over the UI, run the cells below after Step 2."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load backend\n",
    "exec(open('identity_projection_complete.py').read())\n",
    "init_synid_backend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a character from text\n",
    "profile = create_character(\n",
    "    identity_prompt=\"young woman, curly red hair, green eyes, freckles, photorealistic\",\n",
    "    anchor_seed=42,\n",
    "    num_identity_tokens=4,\n",
    "    train_steps=250,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show anchor image\n",
    "display(profile.anchor_image)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Attach UNet adapters\n",
    "adapters = attach_identity_adapters(pipe.unet, identity_dim=768, scale=0.5)\n",
    "hooks    = register_adapter_hooks(pipe.unet)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train adapter on bootstrap images\n",
    "train_adapter_on_bootstrap(\n",
    "    pipe.unet, pipe.vae, pipe.text_encoder, pipe.tokenizer,\n",
    "    adapters, profile.identity_tokens,\n",
    "    [c.image for c in profile.bootstrap_candidates],\n",
    "    [c.prompt for c in profile.bootstrap_candidates],\n",
    "    profile.base_identity_embedding,\n",
    "    train_steps=200, lr=1e-5,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Generate variations\n",
    "expressions = [\n",
    "    \"bright smile, cheerful\",\n",
    "    \"surprised, wide eyes\",\n",
    "    \"serious, focused gaze\",\n",
    "    \"neutral expression, studio lighting\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "images = []\n",
    "for i, expr in enumerate(expressions):\n",
    "    prompt = profile.character_core_prompt + \", \" + expr\n",
    "    img = generate_with_adapter(\n",
    "        profile.identity_tokens, prompt, profile.pose_image,\n",
    "        pipe.unet, pipe, seed=5001 + i,\n",
    "        identity_scale=adaptive_identity_scale(prompt),\n",
    "        generation_steps=30,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    images.append(img)\n",
    "\n",
    "display(show_grid(images, cols=2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run quick evaluation (4 expressions, CLIP + ArcFace scores)\n",
    "exec(open('evaluation_harness.py').read())\n",
    "results = eval_quick(profile, adapters_active=True)\n",
    "print(f\"CLIP identity: {results['clip_mean']:.4f}\")\n",
    "arc = results['arc_mean']\n",
    "print(f\"ArcFace: {arc:.4f}\" if arc is not None else \"ArcFace: N/A\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Save checkpoint\n",
    "save_checkpoint(profile, adapters, \"/content/checkpoints/my_character\")\n",
    "print(\"Saved.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
